# BYOPH Project - Exclude Blog Post Supporting Content
# Keep: Code samples, detection rules, technical components
# Ignore: Articles, diagrams, polls, social media content

# ============================================
# Blog Post Content - Articles
# ============================================

# All article markdown files
#Articles/articles/
#Articles/articles/*.md

# All diagrams and visual content
#Articles/diagrams/
#Articles/diagrams/*.md
#Articles/diagrams/**/*.png
#Articles/diagrams/**/*.svg
#Articles/diagrams/**/*.jpg

# Supporting content for social media
Articles/supporting-content/
Articles/supporting-content/*.md

# GitHub README files (if you want to exclude these too)
#Articles/github-readme/
#Articles/github-readme/**/*.md

# Alternative: If you want to keep the main Articles README but exclude subdirectories
# Uncomment the line below and comment out the wildcard patterns above
# Articles/README.md

# ============================================
# Optional: Other Common Exclusions
# ============================================

# Windows thumbnail cache
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db

# macOS files
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride

# Editor/IDE files
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp
*.log

# Build artifacts (if applicable)
*.exe
*.dll
*.obj
*.pdb
!samples/**/*.exe

# ============================================
# Jekyll / GitHub Pages
# ============================================

# Jekyll build output
_site/
.sass-cache/
.jekyll-cache/
.jekyll-metadata

# Ruby dependencies
Gemfile.lock
.bundle/
vendor/

# ============================================
# Notes
# ============================================
# This .gitignore excludes all blog post content while keeping:
# - Code samples (handlers, registration files, invocation tests)
# - Detection rules (Sigma, Sysmon configs, hunting queries)
# - Technical documentation needed for the repository
#
# To include specific files, use the ! prefix (e.g., !important-file.md)

